author: Slidebean
description:
What Elon Musk’s $600B net worth actually represents.

Musk’s historic net worth milestone isn’t a measure of liquidity or cash accumulation.
It’s a snapshot of investor confidence across a small set of highly valued companies.

In modern markets, extreme wealth isn’t stored, it fluctuates.
What we’re really measuring isn’t money, but belief at scale.

title: Elon Musk is worth $600 billion  but that number isn’t what you think

author: Slidebean
description:
Why AI leadership is now decided by infrastructure, not algorithms.

As AI models scale, the limiting factors are no longer software breakthroughs but physical constraints: data center capacity, energy availability, and specialized hardware supply chains.

With trillion dollar capital commitments and energy intensive facilities becoming standard, competitive advantage in AI is shifting from research labs to infrastructure ownership.
The next phase of AI competition will be decided by who can build, the power and the fastest.

title: The real AI race isn’t software, it’s infrastructure.
